Business Secrets mean any technical, financial, commercial or any other information owned and treated as business secrets by one Party and/or its subsidiaries or affiliates, which have the following attributes:

(i) It is unknown to the public;

(ii) It may generate economic benefit for its owner;

(iii) It is practical; and

(iv) It is treated as business secrets with appropriate protection measures by its owner.
